# --- Multi-target local dev (golden | mozarthitos | espaciozenit) ---
# `npm run dev` pregunta qué entorno usar y copia el archivo elegido a `.env.local`.
# Mantené copias en la raíz del repo (gitignored):
#   .env.local.golden          — Golden English / proyecto principal
#   .env.local.mozarthitos    — otro Supabase / NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL (preview mozarthitos)
#   .env.local.espaciozenit  — Espacio Zenit (otro proyecto Vercel / Supabase opcional)
# Atajos: npm run dev:golden | npm run dev:mozarthitos | npm run dev:espaciozenit
# Sin terminal: GE_DEV_TARGET=golden|mozarthitos|espaciozenit npm run dev
# Migración desde un solo .env.local:  cp .env.local .env.local.golden
# Traer env desde Vercel → archivos prefijados (requiere vercel login):
#   npm run pull:env:golden          # Development (golden tiene vars ahí)
#   npm run pull:env:mozarthitos    # Production según vercel-targets (Sensitive → valores "")
#   npm run pull:env:espaciozenit # Igual; completá orgId/projectId en vercel-targets antes
# Las variables “Sensitive” en Production/Preview NO las puede leer la CLI (KEY vacío).
# Para mozarthitos local: duplicá las claves en Development sin Sensitive, o pegá desde dashboard.
# https://vercel.com/docs/environment-variables/sensitive-environment-variables
# Preview: node scripts/pull-vercel-env.mjs mozarthitos --preview -y
# El script escribe .vercel/project.json solo durante el pull y lo restaura después.

# Otro Vercel + otra BD: leer marca y overrides del tema con este slug (servidor).
# Requiere SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY. En Golden no definas esto; activá solo el tema en CMS.
# El wizard /setup/first-run persiste en la misma fila que este slug (no solo en is_active).
# SITE_BRAND_THEME_SLUG=mozarthitos
# SITE_BRAND_THEME_SLUG=espaciozenit
# SITE_BRAND_THEME_SLUG=nago

# Supabase (URL + one publishable/anon key — required for browser + middleware)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Legacy JWT “anon” key (API Settings → anon public) — still widely used
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...

# New Supabase “publishable” key (sb_publishable_…) — dashboard may only show this
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# Optional fallbacks
# SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
# SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=sb_publishable_...

# Supabase service role — solo servidor (importación masiva / admin API). Nunca NEXT_PUBLIC_
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-secret

# Payment gateways (Flow Chile, etc.): AES-256 key used to encrypt provider API secrets at rest in Postgres (32 raw bytes as Base64).
# Generate: openssl rand -base64 32
# Flow webhooks need a public HTTPS URL (set NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL correctly in each environment; use a tunnel such as ngrok for local sandbox callbacks).
# PAYMENT_GATEWAY_SECRET_ENCRYPTION_KEY=

# Supabase — server-only Postgres URL for scripts (psql migrations, tooling).
# Direct (default in dashboard copy):
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.your-project.supabase.co:5432/postgres
# If `nslookup db.your-project.supabase.co` fails but `your-project.supabase.co` works:
# Dashboard → Connect → Session pooler (host aws-0-<REGION>.pooler.supabase.com, user postgres.<ref>).
# https://supabase.com/docs/guides/database/connecting-to-postgres#pooler-session-mode
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@db.your-project.supabase.co:5432/postgres

# Resend (server-only)
RESEND_API_KEY=re_your_api_key_here
# Verified sender domain in Resend (e.g. notifications@yourdomain.com) — required for outbound mail
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=notifications@yourdomain.com

# App — use the real origin in production (SEO: canonical, OG, sitemap, JSON-LD)
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Skip forcing `/dashboard/admin/site-setup` (greenfield wizard gate). Use only for CI/e2e.
# SKIP_INITIAL_SITE_SETUP=1

# Browser: extra login trace logs (`[goldenenglish:login]`). Failures always use console.error regardless.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEBUG_LOGIN=true

# Minors: profile self-edit of sensitive fields is blocked in Postgres when a tutor link exists (migration 015).
# Supabase Auth login email is not covered by that trigger; use an Auth hook or admin-only email change if you need the same rule for auth email.

# Vercel KV / Upstash (optional) — CSV import progress in admin. Create a KV or Redis store in Vercel → link env vars.
# Without these, import still works synchronously (no live row counter).
# KV_REST_API_URL=
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=

# Cron (e.g. Vercel Cron → GET /api/cron/churn-inactivity) — protect the route
# CRON_SECRET=your-long-random-secret

# WhatsApp Cloud API (optional — class reminder urgent messages). Template must match body param count/order.
# WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID=
# WHATSAPP_CLASS_REMINDER_TEMPLATE_NAME=

# Google Maps — browser autocomplete + client geocoder preview on profile address (NEXT_PUBLIC_ = exposed to client; restrict key by HTTP referrer in Google Cloud).
# Enable Maps JavaScript API, Places API (New) / autocomplete widget, and Geocoding API for the same key.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
# Map ID for vector maps + Advanced Marker preview (home address map). Create in Cloud Console → Map Management; falls back to DEMO_MAP_ID if unset (testing only).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_MAP_ID=

# Public registration — when a minor leaves the student's email blank, we assign local-part@MAIL_TENANT (server-only; no scheme, e.g. alumnos.your-institute.cl).
# MAIL_TENANT=alumnos.your-institute.cl
